<item>
            <title>[PIG-637] limit with order by is broken in local mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-637</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Shubham, could you take a look.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following script when ran in local mode just ignores the limit and outputs the entire data set:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a = load &apos;studenttab10k&apos; as (name, age,gpa);&lt;br/&gt;
b = order a by name;&lt;br/&gt;
c = limit b 10;&lt;br/&gt;
dump c;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same script works fine in MR mode&lt;/p&gt;</description>
